That's true.

00:02:01.496 --> 00:02:02.497
Then maybe it's for the best

00:02:02.539 --> 00:02:05.375
if we get your uniform
made a little bit bigger.

00:02:05.417 --> 00:02:06.376
[PROPRIETRESS A]
I have to say,

00:02:06.418 --> 00:02:09.087
finding out you've been
married was a shock, Yor!

00:02:09.129 --> 00:02:11.465
I get not wanting to make
a big deal about it and all,

00:02:11.506 --> 00:02:12.633
but you could've
at least told me

00:02:12.674 --> 00:02:14.217
the last time you were here!

00:02:14.259 --> 00:02:17.095
I'm sorry, it must've
just slipped my mind.

00:02:17.137 --> 00:02:18.972
And to think that your
adorable daughter

00:02:19.014 --> 00:02:21.433
is going to the prestigious
Eden College.

00:02:21.475 --> 00:02:23.185
Congrats, dear!

00:02:23.226 --> 00:02:25.270
Thanks a crunch!

00:02:25.312 --> 00:02:28.065
Is it safe to assume
you're an Eden College alum?

00:02:28.106 --> 00:02:31.193
No. I attended a little
school out in the country.

00:02:31.234 --> 00:02:33.779
[PROPRIETRESS A] Oh, then you're
going to want to be careful.

00:02:33.820 --> 00:02:35.322
You could say there's
something of a wall

00:02:35.364 --> 00:02:36.740
between the alumni families

00:02:36.782 --> 00:02:39.034
and the first-generation
ones at that school.

00:02:39.076 --> 00:02:40.952
